FT  04 JUL 94 / Warning on cost of civil court cases
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Too many civil court cases cost more than the value of the dispute, the Law
Society says today.
Even where legal action would be cost-effective, many people cannot afford
it and are not eligible for legal aid.
The Law Society highlights these as serious problems in the civil justice
system in its submission to Lord Mackay, the Lord Chancellor, who is
reviewing expenditure on civil litigation and legal aid.
