FT  04 JUL 94 / Call to build new nuclear plants
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government's power-generation policy runs the risk of exchanging an
undue dependence on coal for an undue reliance on gas unless new
pressurised-water reactor nuclear plants are built, the cross-party European
Policy Forum warns today.
It says the government must make up its mind whether the security of supply
and environmental benefits make it appropriate for it to provide the support
needed to draw in private finance for a new PWR power station, for example
by underwriting risk insurance.
