FT  04 JUL 94 / Low inflation will not help wage rises says report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Higher pay rises fuelled by tax increases have not materialised, and the
prospect of continuing low inflation in coming months creates little
likelihood of substantial wage inflation, says the latest report from the
independent pay analysts Industrial Relations Services, David Goodhart
writes.
In spite of some anxiety from government and business leaders about the
recent upward trend in overall earnings, IRS figures show pay settlements at
2.5 per cent in the three months to the end of May. Half of the 153
settlements recorded by IRS in the quarter to the end of May fall between 2
per cent and 3 per cent.
Just over two-fifths of bargaining groups secured higher pay rises than a
year earlier, but a similar proportion agreed lower rises.
A group of insurance staff at the Iron Trades Insurance Group, the UK mutual
insurance company, have rejected a 2.5 per cent pay offer and are planning a
one-day strike on Thursday.
