FT  04 JUL 94 / World Cup '94: Kantor seeks break for US
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
No game has received more anticipatory ink and airtime than today's between
Brazil and the US. But the best word comes from Mickey Kantor, US trade
representative and baseball freak, caught with his family at the
Spain-Switzerland game.
He fancied Spain, though not, he insisted, because Swiss markets are
insufficiently open.
When Brazil declared independence early last century, the first country to
afford recognition was the US. Is it not time, Kantor wonders, for Brazil to
acknowledge that favour, especially since it is playing the US national team
on the 218th anniversary of US independence?
