<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JUL 94 / World Cup '94: Shock follows Escobar murder
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Colombian police reported the arrest of two suspects and said two others
were being sought in the murder of national team player Andres Escobar.
Twenty-seven year-old Escobar, whose own goal in Colombia's game against the
US led to his team's 2-1 upset defeat and contributed to their elimination
from the tournament, was shot 12 times on Saturday as he left a bar in
Medellin, Colombia's third-largest city.
President Cesar Gaviria told mourners yesterday at the player's funeral,
that he was the victim of 'absurd violence' afflicting Colombia.
Fifa said in a statement that it was 'profoundly horrified and dismayed' by
the slaying, while Italian coach Arrigo Sacchi summed up the shock that
reverberated around the soccer community. 'The unjustified death of a young
player means that soccer is not only and no longer a sporting event, but
something whose importance goes beyond our beliefs.'
