<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 94 / Dockers lose redundancy case
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Twenty-six workers sacked from Goole docks on Humberside after industrial
action lost a four-year battle for redundancy money yesterday.
Three Court of Appeal judges dismissed by a majority an appeal aimed at
reinstating their entitlement to compensation. The 26 were dismissed in
April 1990 after an overtime ban in protest at a new bonus scheme. They said
that their sackings were a 'set-up' to avoid paying redundancy.
Lord Justice Dillon said that the industrial action in support of the bonus
generated the dismissals and the subsequent decision to use contract labour.
</TEXT>
