<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity Futures and Options Trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY BYLAND
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
It was a slack session in the derivatives markets, and although the stock
index future contract provided a confident lead for equities, trading volume
was not heavy, writes Terry Byland. The September contract held at a small
premium to the cash market, although the closing quotation of 2,945 on
September showed a discount of about 4 to fair value.
In traded options, the picture was much the same. Overall volume dipped to
22,311 contracts from more than 29,000 on Thursday. Only 8,622 contracts
were recorded in the FT-SE option.
</TEXT>
