FT  02 JUL 94 / Letters to the Editor: Concern for the homeless
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr TED HILL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Mr John Gummer, the environment secretary ('Gummer moots council
housing change', June 30), leaves me with deep concerns over the future for
homeless people. His statement that local authorities should not
automatically provide accommodation for homeless people leaves little hope
for the 135,000 households officially accepted as homeless last year, nor
for the 8,000-plus people who sleep rough every night, the 5,000 families in
bed and breakfast accommodation, or the 38,800 families in other temporary
accommodation.
With the government's green paper on homelessness generating controversial
debate, I await uneasily the white paper later this year.
Ted Hill,
Homes for Homeless People,
90-92 Bromham Road,
Bedford, Beds MK40 2QH
