FT  02 JUL 94 / British Coal to sell largest subsidiary
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Coal is to offer Coal Products, its largest business subsidiary, for
sale.
The Chesterfield-based company is the UK's largest manufacturer of solid
smokeless fuels and foundry coke. Its annual turnover of Pounds 130m makes
it larger than some of the regional mining businesses into which British
Coal will be divided for privatisation.
Coal Products has four plants and employs about 550 people. Last year's
profits of Pounds 12m before tax were three times the previous year's.
British Coal said it had received more than a dozen expressions of interest
from potential buyers, including a management buy-out proposal.
